" Learning advices
"""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""
A Summary from [ https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ke7SfUFvvxo ]

1. Learn to use vim help
  - Spend a few minitues a day in vim help.

2. Keep a cheetsheet
  - 7 to 10 commands on your cheetsheet.
  - Be aware of these commands' existence and opportunities you can use them.

3. Keep track of your common mistakes

4. Learn all single letter commands
   [ http://hea-www.harvard.edu/~fine/Tech/vi.html ]

"""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""
" My vim cheetsheet
"""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""
" Command due to vimrc configuration.
1. \w : open a url link on browser from vim.

2. <F5> : trim off all trailing whitespace characters of every line.

3. <leader><cr> : turn off search highlighting for current search only

4. <F4> : toggle search highlighting for the whole session.

5. Ctrl j : Move a line or the selected text under the cursor down
   Ctrl k : Move a line or the selected text under the cursor up

" Built-in Commands
1. Shift N to search in the "opposite" direction.
2. `. will take you to the last change you made.

"""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""
